verses.text_plain: Every wise woman buildeth her house: but the foolish plucketh it down with her hands.
verses.verse_html: 1Every wise woman buildeth her house: but the foolish plucketh it down with her hands.

verses.text_plain: He that walketh in his uprightness feareth the Lord: but he that is perverse in his ways despiseth him.
verses.verse_html: 2He that walketh in his uprightness feareth the Lord: but he that is perverse in his ways despiseth him.

verses.text_plain: In the mouth of the foolish is a rod of pride: but the lips of the wise shall preserve them.
verses.verse_html: 3In the mouth of the foolish is a rod of pride: but the lips of the wise shall preserve them.

verses.text_plain: Where no oxen are, the crib is clean: but much increase is by the strength of the ox.
verses.verse_html: 4Where no oxen are, the crib is clean: but much increase is by the strength of the ox.

verses.text_plain: A faithful witness will not lie: but a false witness will utter lies.
verses.verse_html: 5A faithful witness will not lie: but a false witness will utter lies.

verses.text_plain: A scorner seeketh wisdom, and findeth it not: but knowledge is easy unto him that understandeth.
verses.verse_html: 6A scorner seeketh wisdom, and findeth it not: but knowledge is easy unto him that understandeth.

verses.text_plain: Go from the presence of a foolish man, when thou perceivest not in him the lips of knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 7Go from the presence of a foolish man, when thou perceivest not in him the lips of knowledge.

verses.text_plain: The wisdom of the prudent is to understand his way: but the folly of fools is deceit.
verses.verse_html: 8The wisdom of the prudent is to understand his way: but the folly of fools is deceit.

verses.text_plain: Fools make a mock at sin: but among the righteous there is favour.
verses.verse_html: 9Fools make a mock at sin: but among the righteous there is favour.

verses.text_plain: The heart knoweth his own bitterness; and a stranger doth not intermeddle with his joy.
verses.verse_html:
10The heart knoweth his own bitterness; and a stranger doth not intermeddle with his joy.
 his own: Heb. the bitterness of his soul

footnotes.body_text: his own: Heb. the bitterness of his soul
footnotes.body_html: his own: Heb. the bitterness of his soul

verses.text_plain: The house of the wicked shall be overthrown: but the tabernacle of the upright shall flourish.
verses.verse_html: 11The house of the wicked shall be overthrown: but the tabernacle of the upright shall flourish.

verses.text_plain: There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.
verses.verse_html: 12There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.

verses.text_plain: Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful; and the end of that mirth is heaviness.
verses.verse_html: 13Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful; and the end of that mirth is heaviness.

verses.text_plain: The backslider in heart shall be filled with his own ways: and a good man shall be satisfied from himself.
verses.verse_html: 14The backslider in heart shall be filled with his own ways: and a good man shall be satisfied from himself.

verses.text_plain: The simple believeth every word: but the prudent man looketh well to his going.
verses.verse_html: 15The simple believeth every word: but the prudent man looketh well to his going.

verses.text_plain: A wise man feareth, and departeth from evil: but the fool rageth, and is confident.
verses.verse_html: 16A wise man feareth, and departeth from evil: but the fool rageth, and is confident.

verses.text_plain: He that is soon angry dealeth foolishly: and a man of wicked devices is hated.
verses.verse_html: 17He that is soon angry dealeth foolishly: and a man of wicked devices is hated.

verses.text_plain: The simple inherit folly: but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 18The simple inherit folly: but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.

verses.text_plain: The evil bow before the good; and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.
verses.verse_html: 19The evil bow before the good; and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.

verses.text_plain: The poor is hated even of his own neighbour: but the rich hath many friends.
verses.verse_html:
20The poor is hated even of his own neighbour: but the rich hath many friends.
 the rich: Heb. many are the lovers of the rich

footnotes.body_text: the rich: Heb. many are the lovers of the rich
footnotes.body_html: the rich: Heb. many are the lovers of the rich

verses.text_plain: He that despiseth his neighbour sinneth: but he that hath mercy on the poor, happy is he.
verses.verse_html: 21He that despiseth his neighbour sinneth: but he that hath mercy on the poor, happy is he.

verses.text_plain: Do they not err that devise evil? but mercy and truth shall be to them that devise good.
verses.verse_html: 22Do they not err that devise evil? but mercy and truth shall be to them that devise good.

verses.text_plain: In all labour there is profit: but the talk of the lips tendeth only to penury.
verses.verse_html: 23In all labour there is profit: but the talk of the lips tendeth only to penury.

verses.text_plain: The crown of the wise is their riches: but the foolishness of fools is folly.
verses.verse_html: 24The crown of the wise is their riches: but the foolishness of fools is folly.

verses.text_plain: A true witness delivereth souls: but a deceitful witness speaketh lies.
verses.verse_html: 25A true witness delivereth souls: but a deceitful witness speaketh lies.

verses.text_plain: In the fear of the Lord is strong confidence: and his children shall have a place of refuge.
verses.verse_html: 26In the fear of the Lord is strong confidence: and his children shall have a place of refuge.

tokens.text: shall have a place of refuge

verses.text_plain: The fear of the Lord is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.
verses.verse_html: 27The fear of the Lord is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.

verses.text_plain: In the multitude of people is the kings honour: but in the want of people is the destruction of the prince.
verses.verse_html: 28In the multitude of people is the kings honour: but in the want of people is the destruction of the prince.

verses.text_plain: He that is slow to wrath is of great understanding: but he that is hasty of spirit exalteth folly.
verses.verse_html:
29He that is slow to wrath is of great understanding: but he that is hasty of spirit exalteth folly.
 hasty: Heb. short of spirit

footnotes.body_html: hasty: Heb. short of spirit

verses.text_plain: A sound heart is the life of the flesh: but envy the rottenness of the bones.
verses.verse_html: 30A sound heart is the life of the flesh: but envy the rottenness of the bones.

verses.text_plain: He that oppresseth the poor reproacheth his Maker: but he that honoureth him hath mercy on the poor.
verses.verse_html: 31He that oppresseth the poor reproacheth his Maker: but he that honoureth him hath mercy on the poor.

verses.text_plain: The wicked is driven away in his wickedness: but the righteous hath hope in his death.
verses.verse_html: 32The wicked is driven away in his wickedness: but the righteous hath hope in his death.

verses.text_plain: Wisdom resteth in the heart of him that hath understanding: but that which is in the midst of fools is made known.
verses.verse_html: 33Wisdom resteth in the heart of him that hath understanding: but that which is in the midst of fools is made known.

verses.text_plain: Righteousness exalteth a nation: but sin is a reproach to any people.
verses.verse_html:
34Righteousness exalteth a nation: but sin is a reproach to any people.
 to any: Heb. to nations

footnotes.body_html: to any: Heb. to nations

verses.text_plain: The kings favour is toward a wise servant: but his wrath is against him that causeth shame.
verses.verse_html: 35The kings favour is toward a wise servant: but his wrath is against him that causeth shame.
